The paper deals with the problem of estimating a random vector corrupted by additive white Gaussian noise, which is a common problem in information theory and signal processing. Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses bounds and properties of the MMPE, which involves optimization and mathematical analysis, making cs.SI (Systems and Control) a likely sub-category as well. The paper also mentions the use of the MMPE in improving characterizations of the phase transition phenomenon, which is related to statistical physics and machine learning, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) a possible sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of the MMPE in deriving bounds on the second derivative of mutual information, which involves numerical analysis and optimization, making cs.MM (Mathematical Methods) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper mentions the use of interpolation and change of measure bounds, which are common techniques in numerical analysis and optimization, making cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) a possible sub-category as well.
